The Wild Parrots of Telegraph Hill;;85;;95;;G;;A homeless musician's life is transformed after he discovers a flock of wild South American parrots living in San Francisco. How they got there is a mystery, but Mark Bittner forms a bond with the exotic birds through his music and his patient, attentive care. Over time he comes to appreciate their individual identities and makes a case for humans to reevaluate their relationship to animals. When he is forced to leave them, he despairs over the birds' fate.;;Documentary;;Judy Irving;;2004;;NC;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/wild_parrots_of_telegraph_hill